<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="411" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="411">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="411">
This species occurs in numerous sites, both natural and agricultural. In natural sites, 
<bibRefCitation author="Plisko, JD" journalOrPublisher="African Invertebrates" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" pagination="323 - 334" refId="B45" refString="Plisko, JD, 2001. Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae). African Invertebrates 42: 323 - 334" title="Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae)." volume="42" year="2001">Plisko (2001)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species in grasslands, forests, natural bushes and near rivers. In cultivated fields, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Clitellata" family="Rhinodrilidae" genus="Pontoscolex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pontoscolex corenthrurus" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="corenthrurus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="411">Pontoscolex corenthrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected under most crops including maize, sugar-cane, banana, avocado, citrus; some specimens were collected in pine and gum plantations, some even from vegetable gardens (
<bibRefCitation author="Plisko, JD" journalOrPublisher="African Invertebrates" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" pagination="323 - 334" refId="B45" refString="Plisko, JD, 2001. Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae). African Invertebrates 42: 323 - 334" title="Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae)." volume="42" year="2001">Plisko 2001</bibRefCitation>
). This species has been used in experiments at different institutions. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Clitellata" family="Rhinodrilidae" genus="Pontoscolex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pontoscolex corenthrurus" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="corenthrurus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="411">Pontoscolex corenthrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also been collected in polluted sites in KZN (
<bibRefCitation author="Plisko, JD" journalOrPublisher="African Invertebrates" pageId="0" pageNumber="411" pagination="323 - 334" refId="B45" refString="Plisko, JD, 2001. Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae). African Invertebrates 42: 323 - 334" title="Notes on the occurrence of the introduced Pontoscolexcorethrurus (Mueller, 1857) in South Africa (Oligochaeta: Glossoscolecidae)." volume="42" year="2001">Plisko 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The current collection was in sugarcane on one farm only, although we had expected to collect the species in other areas in the KZN Midlands because of its wide occurrence.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
